Lion has a new 'resume' feature that will open applications in the same state they were in. I found this particularly annoying w/ Terminal as cd'ing into my source folder was bypassing my rvm hooks. Initially I turned off the resume feature system-wide: <a title="How to disable resume" href="http://www.macrumors.com/2011/07/20/how-to-disable-lions-resume-feature/" target="_blank">http://www.macrumors.com/2011/07/20/how-to-disable-lions-resume-feature/</a>. However, it still would open in the last folder :/... This morning I found the way to disable resume on a per-application basis <a href="http://osxdaily.com/2011/08/01/turn-off-resume-per-app-in-mac-os-x-lion/" target="_blank">http://osxdaily.com/2011/08/01/turn-off-resume-per-app-in-mac-os-x-lion/</a>

<code>defaults write com.apple.Terminal NSQuitAlwaysKeepsWindows -bool false</code>
