Found <a href="http://ruby.ryanbigg.com/post/1468788928/left-outer-join-with-arel" target="_blank">this post</a> very helpful, so bookmarking here on my blog.

Basic idea is to use .includes(:assoc) instead of joins. <a href="https://github.com/ernie/squeel" target="_blank">Squeel</a> supports a little cleaner DSL so you can do .join(:assoc.outer)

